clinical_study.brief_title: Study Evaluating Neratinib In Combination With Temsirolimus In Subjects With Solid Tumors
clinical_study.official_title: A Phase 1 Study Of Neratinib In Combination With Temsirolimus In Subjects With Solid Tumors

brief_summary.textblock: The primary purpose of this study is to identify the maximum tolerated dose(s) (MTD) of neratinib in combination with temsirolimus in subjects with solid tumors. This study will also include a preliminary evaluation of efficacy, and assessment of pharmacokinetic (PK) parameters of the combination.

primary_outcome.measure: Dose-Limiting Toxicity (DLT) Incidence to Evaluate the Maximum Tolerated Dose (MTD) Toxicity Contour of the Combination of Neratinib and Temsirolimus.
primary_outcome.time_frame: From first dose date to day 28
primary_outcome.description: The Maximum Tolerated Dose (MTD) contour based on dose combinations in which the probability of a DLT was <1/3 (<33.3%). A DLT was defined as any dose-limiting AE related to neratinib + TEMSR as Grade 3 or higher nonhematologic toxicity (except neutropenia) or Grade 3 or higher diarrhea lasting >2 days with optimal antidiarrheal therapy etc.

primary_outcome.time_frame: From first dose date to day 28
primary_outcome.description: Identification of the neratinib high-dose MTD in combination with temsirolimus, and identification of the temsirolimus high-dose MTD in combination with Neratinib.

secondary_outcome.time_frame: From first dose date to progression/death or last tumor assessment
secondary_outcome.description: The best overall response and duration of response (for subjects who achieved an objective response) were described using the data as reported by study center investigators.

secondary_outcome.time_frame: From first dose date to progression/death or last tumor assessment
secondary_outcome.description: Clinical benefit rate by neratinib dose level is the number of subjects with a CR, PR, or SD >= 24 weeks, as determined by RECIST per investigator assessment.

secondary_outcome.description: The objective response rate (ORR) is the number of subjects with a complete response (CR) or partial response (PR).

secondary_outcome.description: AUC tau of neratinib concentrations at various dose levels with various dose levels of temsirolimus.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Pathologic diagnosis of advanced or metastatic solid tumor.
- Measurable disease per Response Criteria in Solid Tumors (RECIST criteria).
- Incurable cancer, with disease progression following at least 1 conventional or standard therapy for locally advanced or metastatic disease.
- Negative pregnancy test for women of child bearing potential.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Chronic treatment with corticosteroids.
- Primary central nervous system (CNS) tumors and active metastases.
- Presence of clinically significant or uncontrolled cardiac disease.
- Significant chronic or recent acute gastrointestinal disorder with diarrhea as a major symptom.
- Symptomatic or prior history of non-infectious interstitial pneumonitis.

outcome.title: Dose-Limiting Toxicity (DLT) Incidence to Evaluate the Maximum Tolerated Dose (MTD) Toxicity Contour of the Combination of Neratinib and Temsirolimus.
outcome.description: The Maximum Tolerated Dose (MTD) contour based on dose combinations in which the probability of a DLT was <1/3 (<33.3%). A DLT was defined as any dose-limiting AE related to neratinib + TEMSR as Grade 3 or higher nonhematologic toxicity (except neutropenia) or Grade 3 or higher diarrhea lasting >2 days with optimal antidiarrheal therapy etc.
outcome.time_frame: From first dose date to day 28
outcome.population: Evaluable subjects for the MTD contour estimation were those who either experienced a DLT within the first 28 days, regardless of the number of doses of treatment received, or received at least 21 doses of neratinib and at least 2 doses of TEMSR in the first 28 days of treatment.
